). Remove supernatant leaving behind ~<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> if the pellet seems loose. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"BB8A5CF0828111E9A587B12DB38CB6C0","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":300,"title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"BE377B90828111E9A587B12DB38CB6C0","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":4,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"D41EEF60828111E9A587B12DB38CB6C0","order_id":4,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":50,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":600,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1176728,"guid":"70D76DD55C6F40C495FD84E345799A1C","previous_id":1176727,"previous_guid":"2A940B3C9EF547C58A9360E64DDA8ADF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"51F22ACAD4F34CADA0C1D68DA88C7402","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Nuclei Isolation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5AC288D17AA4405EA77762BC960D7BDF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Optional: <\/span><span>add <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of Salty-Ez10 Lysis Buffer (supplemented with RNAse Inhibitor 0.2-if pellet is loose0.5 U\/uL), gently resuspend pellet (optional: incubate for <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> on ice for additional lysis). Then centrifuge the nuclei at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> for <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"1C0CBD9C54EF11EBA7170A58A9FEAC2A","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":1,"unit":"mL","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"C30CE05054EF11EB8978EFF04720B9B4","order_id":3,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":300,"title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"061B69D0828211E9A587B12DB38CB6C0","order_id":4,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":300,"title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"090B84E0828211E9A587B12DB38CB6C0","order_id":5,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":4,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":600,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":600},{"id":1176729,"guid":"85F0281166E44BC9B820D42A1BBF4A41","previous_id":1176728,"previous_guid":"70D76DD55C6F40C495FD84E345799A1C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D6523DEA62984826AC6D6E8845DE3198","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Nuclei Wash and Resuspension"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DB076C75B50E4A40BF70655E362E9D38","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After removing the supernatant, add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> of WRB1 (supplemented with RNAse Inhibitor 0.2-0.5 U\/uL) <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">without disturbing the pellet<\/span><span>. Let sit for 5\u2019 on ice and then gently resuspend the pellet<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><span>(this incubation is important to avoid clumping). <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>--> ALTERNATIVELY, resuspend the pellet in WRB2 (supplemented with RNAse Inhibitor 0.2-0.5 U\/uL). The 5\u2019 incubation is optional for this buffer. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">WRB2 is my favorite so far<\/span><span>.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"65B89B70B2A411EB91F6EB32995BDBD7","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":500,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"A7399162AE7140B4BD31DE67E14B71C1","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Warning<\/span><span>: some nucs preps clump when you add WRB1 (this is a known phenomenon with Tris to PBS enchange, hence 5\u2019 on ice helps but not always! It\u2019s sample dependent). In that case use WRB2 (my favorite). Both WRBs are compatible with all 10x kits. <\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"E6699036BA9842C8B13F2CA23C9D050E","order_id":4,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Important:<\/span><span> for 10x Multiome (10x Genomics) add 0.01% Digitonin in the WRB buffers (supplemented with RNAse Inhibitor 0.2-0.5 U\/uL), not during lysis step itself. In this way the time the nuclei is leaky (due to holes caused by Digitonin) is shorter, 5\u2019 on ice is enough to permeabilize nuclei. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Then replace it by the 1x Nuclei Buffer (NB) as indicated in the user guide<\/span><span> (this buffer is essential for ATAC or Multiome kit). <\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":600,"critical":[{"id":12,"title":"Critical step","icon":"CriticalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1176736,"guid":"28FF758EA76F44719015B9EEE84AAADD","previous_id":1176748,"previous_guid":"07BFE070B2A711EB91F6EB32995BDBD7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DBD48D1DCCBB4669B7BA9E935F40854E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Nuclei Wash and Resuspension"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9E31A1FAFB0648C3A8E613F6CA9FBD51","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Check integrity and purity under microscope and count manually or using an automatic counter. For automatic counter I recommend Luna-FL\u2122 Dual Fluorescence Cell Counter and Acridine Orange\/Propidium Iodide (AO\/PI) Cell Viability Kit. This instrument also provides information about size and multiplets which is very useful. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":600,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1176737,"guid":"6C7CF4D16BA9495BA27794DA279472FC","previous_id":1176736,"previous_guid":"28FF758EA76F44719015B9EEE84AAADD","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A60FC4E669DA40408A98950857E3EA6D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Nuclei Wash and Resuspension"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"742A2E9EF00448F399C7BF3D8F2AFAF7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"> Proceed to your amazing snRNA-Seq or Multiome experiment! <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":600,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1176748,"guid":"07BFE070B2A711EB91F6EB32995BDBD7","previous_id":1176729,"previous_guid":"85F0281166E44BC9B820D42A1BBF4A41","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B9F4DA199C8A4E13A34EA22C17E3BD1A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Nuclei Wash and Resuspension"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6C94A67806FB47E08AC7A51F044BCF30","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">If cell debris and large clumps are observed, pass through a cell strainer. For low volume, use a 40 \u03bcm Flowmi Cell Strainer to minimize volume loss.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"95B929A5A96F48A8B003BB6049658010","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>If high amounts of debris or micelles (fat) is present you may perform OptiPrep\u00ae <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\">continuous <\/span><span>gradient as done in DOF (<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.bs99nh96\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.bs99nh96<\/span><\/a><span>, steps 9-12). Use WRBs for washes and resuspension for snRNA-Seq. For Multiome use WRBs for washes and resuspension 1x NB for resuspension. Pass through a cell strainer (e.g., 40 \u03bcm Flowmi Cell Strainer). <\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":600,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[{"id":119307,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Nuclei EZ lysis buffer ","linfor":"","url":"","sku":"EZ PREP NUC-101","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.sigma.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":114},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This is a protocol in development, which means it has not yet tested\/challenged with multiple samples. So, please make sure you take it for a test drive before committing to it. Once you do please share your experience with me via email, Twitter or as a comment.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1620772311}